Finished rereading HATSSSSS. Really good. Better than I remember, even. Probably the best thing this eternally burning dumpster fire of a general has produced, if I'm going to be totally honest. I wish I didn't have to wait so long between updates, though. Leo and Missy are just a ton of fun to read, both of them are really well developed characters. It's like their every character quirk has intrigue behind it, like with Leo's seemingly uncanny hearing that he might've picked up from Missy, or how Missy sees eyes glow in the dark, adding to her whole suite of bestial behaviors. I remember when I first was reading about the story in this general and seeing an odd meme, that HATSSSSS was like a bajillion words where nothing happened. Adds credence to my completely scientifically backed theory that nobody here reads anything, I think, considering one of the most enjoyable aspects of the story for me was how Missy and Leo change over time, slowly becoming a little more like each other, each being a relief to another in different ways. Sure, Leo hasn't fucked her yet. He has hold ups about even saying he loves her (he toootally does). But if that's what irks you about his character or the story, I think you've gotta be retarded or something. It's just not in his nature, and it feels good to see a story that has a protagonist with a solid personality stick to his guns. Not trying to strawman, but I think it's a sentiment I occasionally see when seeing people talk about the story. And I'm not trying to shit on any stories with Anon type characters either, but Leo has his own past with his own traumas that form up the character he is now, which makes him a cut above the rest in my book.
Anyway, words words words autism over. I just like the story, I guess.

I don't know about dogs, but in the American South there has been a longstanding shady practice in the unlicensed pet distributor market where cat breeders will, with absolutely no veterinary supervision or wherewithal, excise the tails of newborn kittens down to around a third of their length in order to advertise them as "bobcats" for an increased profit. Since the idea of domesticated true bobcats have been seen as something of a novelty in the South for many decades, these people have capitalized on this through both selective breeding and barbaric amateur docking procedures to produce kittens with often mutilated, nonfunctional tails that can produce infections, cause lifelong pain and balance issues so that they can be advertised as "exotic." And these practices have only barely started being called out. Real sad shit.
